It can be used to find files and directories and perform subsequent operations on them. It supports searching by file, folder, name, creation date, modification date, owner and permissions.

$ find . -empty                                         # find all empty folders and files
$ find . -type f -empty
$ find . -name FILE_NAME
$ find . -type f -name FILE_NAME
$ find . -type f -name "*.FORMAT"
EG: find . -type f -name "*.php"
$ find ./FOLDER_NAME -empty                             # find all empty folders and files in the entered directory or sub-directories
$ find ./FOLDER_NAME -name FILE_NAME
$ find ./FOLDER_NAME -name *.FORMAT
EG: find ./FOLDER_NAME -name *.txt
$ find ./ -type f -name "*.FORMAT"
EG: find ./ -type f -name "*.txt" 
$ find /FOLDER_NAME -type f -empty
$ find /FOLDER_NAME -type d -empty
$ find / -name FILE_NAME
$ find /FOLDER_NAME -name FILE_NAME
$ find / -type d -name FOLDER_NAME
$ find /home -user USER_NAME
$ find / -user USER_NAME -name FILE_NAME
$ find /FOLDER_NAME -type f -name ".*"                  # Hidden Files
